ĹTo honour
Thomas J. Johnston of San Francisco
Who visited these gardens as a Commander in the
US Navy during the Normandy Landings and
later with his family and President of his company"Ń
ĺFor Gwyneth and Arnold, remembered with love
by their children and grandchildren
"Nature's economy shall be the base for our own,
for it is immutable, but ours is secondary" Linnaeus 1740"Ň
¬As a small boy not far from this very spot, he began running and did not stop
Far across the globe he ran, this beloved, crazy, brilliant man
He loved wine. music and the southern sun, he always gave his best to everyone
He is much missed and that he should, for our south London boy did good
Vincent Hancock 1944-2006"Õ
 in Loving Memory of BRIAN MIST Naturalist and Conservationist
For his Work and Dedication to the Park
Who Died 8th May 2002 - Age 65
Sadly missed by his wife Rosie and son Bradley and all his friends"Ō
ŐIN TREASURED MEMORY OF MY DARLING HUSBAND
FRANIE DANIELS 25.10.1910 - 15.2.1992
HIS BUSINESS WAS IN MOUNT STREET
TOGETHER WE SHARED THIS SECRET GARDEN
FOR EVER AND ALWAYS AND ALL ETERNITY YOUR SHELAGH"Ō
ŐPeter & Muriel Kenny
We wrote your name In the sand, but the waves washed it away
We wrote your name in the sky, but the clouds blew it away
So we wrote your name in our hearts and forever it will stay"ŕ
◊In memory of
William, Marquess of Hartington
Coldstream Guards
Killed in action whilst serving with 5th Battalion
Belgium September 1944
This seat is given by his brother and sisters
Andrew, Elizabeth and Anne"Ř
ōIn Loving Memory of Georgi "Porgy" Todorov 1978 2005
"It's not the years in your life that count...
It's the life in your years" We will never forget your
smile, you are forever our inspiration. We miss you Porg x"ŗ
